ey, Lithuania, and other countries;• Lenin had little regard for Trotsky's judgment on important matters and relied heavily on Stalin;• Lenin assiduously tracked dissident intellectuals and urged repressive action or deportation;• Lenin launched a political offensive against the Orthodox Church, ordering that priests who resisted seizure of church property be shot--"the more the better."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aHeads of statexArchivesxSoviet Union. 0aHeads of statezSoviet UnionvArchives. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aBuranov, Yury A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPipes, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030016364340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300163643423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300163643/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles